                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote script="Ethiopic" xml:id="h1">
                                <desc>Written in a fine, bold hand. Cues (letters and numerals), in
                                    black, on the left and internal margin of some folios (e.g.
                                    <locus target="#2r"/>, <locus target="#23v"/>, <locus target="#41r"/>). Presence of paragraph signs. Crux ansata and coronis (e.g. <locus target="#66v"/>, <locus target="#77r"/>, <locus target="#116r"/>). Chains of punctuation signs (esp. nine dots asterisks with lines in between) used sometimes as text dividers.</desc>
                                <date notBefore="1400" notAfter="1499"/>
                                <seg type="rubrication">A few lines, or groups of two lines, on the incipit page or incipit of each text. Ethiopic numerals (entirely in red) and elements of punctuations and paragraphs signs. Decoration signs (coronis and crux ansata), some entirely in red (e.g. <locus target="#66v"/>, <locus target="#116r"/>), some in black end red. Marginal notes (entirely in red).</seg>
                            </handNote>

